JqueryAutocompleteHelper
==================

This helper is to use jquery's autocomplete to look up a value and insert it into a hidden form field.  Useful for linking a join model to another model.


Example
=======

This plugin assumes:

The model being search has a method called display_name

view:

<% form_for @organization do |f| %>
  <p>
    <%= f.label :person_id %><br />
   <%= auto_complete_field(:organization, :person) %>
  </p>
....
<script type="text/javascript">
<%= yield :runview %>
</script>


controller for person:

def index
  @people = Person.search(params[:q])

  respond_to do |format|
    format.html  { ... }
    format.xml  { ... }
    format.js { render :text => @people.map { |c| "#{c.display_name}|#{c.id}\n" } }
  end
end

